<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Simple Homepage</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
</head>
<style>
    body, h1, h2, p {
  margin: 0;
  padding: 0;
}

body {
  font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
  background-color: #f0f0f0;
  color: #333;
  text-align: center;
}

header {
  background-color: #4CAF50;
  color: white;
  padding: 20px;
}

.content {
  padding: 20px;
}

footer {
  background-color: #333;
  color: white;
  padding: 10px 0;
  position: fixed;
  bottom: 0;
  width: 100%;
}
</style>
<body>
  <header>
    <h1>Welcome to My Simple Homepage</h1>
  </header>

  <section class="content">
    <h2>About Me</h2>
    <p>This is a paragraph about me. You can add more content here.</p>
  </section>
  Copy the HTML code into a file named index.html and the CSS code into a file named styles.css. Make sure both files are in the same directory.
  Open index.html in a web browser to see your simple homepage.
  You can customize the content inside the <header>, <section>, and <footer> tags to suit your needs. Add more sections, images, links, etc., as required.
  <footer>
    <p>&copy; 2024 My Homepage. All rights reserved.</p>
  </footer>
</body>
</html>